The paper deals with the problem of multiple mobile agents collaborating to deliver a message in a graph, which is a classic problem in multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The agents have limited energy, which is a constraint on their movement, making it relevant to robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves finding a feasible movement schedule for the agents, which is a scheduling problem and can be related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes algorithms for solving the problem, which involves resource allocation and optimization, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
